  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.3-stable`\r\nOS & Version: `Ubuntu 16.04.4`\r\nCommit hash : `329ac18ef617d0238f71637bffe78f028b0f13f7`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nSeems that chaindata must be about 68-72Gb (according to https://etherscan.io/chart2/chaindatasizefast)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm synced to 5533382 block and already have about 79Gb of chaindata\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nPerform removedb and run geth with following params:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n./geth --nousb --syncmode \"fast\" --cache 2048 --rpc --rpcapi personal,web3,eth,net\r\n```\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ndu -h ~/.ethereum/\r\n16M     /home/eth/.ethereum/geth/nodes\r\n78G     /home/eth/.ethereum/geth/chaindata\r\n233M    /home/eth/.ethereum/geth/ethash\r\n79G     /home/eth/.ethereum/geth\r\n1.8M    /home/eth/.ethereum/keystore\r\n79G     /home/eth/.ethereum/\r\n```",
